The great Inſtances of Prerogative and Majeſty in making War, creating Judges, and, which we might think the proper

work of the Sanhedrim, the ordering of Church-Affairs, depoſing ill Miniſters, and the like; That all this was done ſometimes immediately by the Kings themſelves, muſt be evident to any body who will be at the pains to go thro' the Hiſtory of thoſe Princes in the Books of Samuel, Kings and Chronicles. Nay, the very putting a Prophet to death, or diſcharging him out of Priſon, This alſo was the King's Act, as we ſee in the Example of Zedekiah and Jeremiah;
               Jerem. 38. and this without the Rebuke or Murmur of that Aſſembly, tho' then the King's Circumſtances were very low, and might have encouraged them to it.
